headline: eBay just sent a message its workforce will not forget
summary: eBay (EBAY) is cutting approximately 800 jobs, or roughly 6% of its global workforce, as the e-commerce company realigns its structure around long-term strategic priorities. The San Jose-based company confirmed the layoffs Thursday, marking its third round of job cuts in three years. The cuts come ...
